  "body": "### Description\r\nAs a mainnet staker, I want to increase the transaction pool size to see if it improves Besu's very poor rate of inclusion of transactions in blocks with its default settings.\r\n\r\nThe [default](https://besu.hyperledger.org/en/stable/public-networks/reference/cli/options/#tx-pool-max-size) for `tx-pool-hashes-max-size` is 4096, and I constantly see the Tx pool butting up against that limit in my metrics (`besu_transaction_pool_transactions`).\r\n\r\nI wanted to try a modest increase to 6144, so added a line to my config file:\r\n\r\n```\r\ntx-pool-hashes-max-size=6144\r\n```\r\n\r\nHowever, after restarting the `besu_transaction_pool_transactions` metric continues to sit at or just below 4096. It never exceeds 4096. I am confident that the config file was picked up as Besu recognised a different change I made to it at the same time.\r\n\r\n### Acceptance Criteria\r\n* Chainging `tx-pool-hashes-max-size` results in a corresponding change to the size of the transaction pool.\r\n\r\n### Steps to Reproduce (Bug)\r\n1. Run Besu on mainnet with `tx-pool-hashes-max-size=6144`\r\n2. Observe that the size of the transaction pool never exceeds the default value of 4096.\r\n\r\nI tried once with\r\n\r\n```\r\ntx-pool-hashes-max-size=6144\r\n```\r\n\r\nAnd once with\r\n\r\n```\r\ntx-pool-hashes-max-size=\"6144\"\r\n```\r\n\r\nNeither was effective.\r\n\r\n### Versions (Add all that apply)\r\n* Software version: besu/v22.7.5/linux-x86_64/openjdk-java-17\r\n",
